      passage: `The novelist John Crowley has been championed by figures such as the poet James Merrill and the critic Harold Bloom. In an afterword to Crowley's novel <i>Little, Big</i>, Bloom praises the way the book blends what Friedrich Schiller called the “naive” and “sentimental” modes of literature, showing that a single work can be both.`,
