      passage: `Because sending equipment to Mars is expensive and risky, scientists test their devices using “simulants”&mdash;materials engineered to mimic Martian soil. One such simulant, Mars Mojave, is made from lava found in California's Mojave Desert. Using simulants helps scientists evaluate how well their devices will handle the surface when operated on Mars.`,
